Devon is one of England's most beautiful and economically diverse counties. As an SEO consultant working with Devon businesses, I help companies across the county — from Exeter to Plymouth, Torquay to Barnstaple — build organic search visibility that drives real commercial results without the cost and complexity of a traditional agency.

Whether you run a tourism business on the South Devon coast, a professional services firm in Exeter, or a food and drink brand with national ambitions, I provide senior-level SEO strategy built around your specific market and goals.

## Devon's economy and the digital opportunity

Devon's economy is more varied than many people realise. Exeter is the county's commercial hub, home to a growing tech sector, the Met Office, and the University of Exeter — one of the UK's top research universities. Plymouth brings naval heritage, a strong maritime sector, and the University of Plymouth. Across the county, tourism, agriculture, food production, and professional services form the backbone of the local economy.

Devon's tourism industry alone is worth billions annually, with Dartmoor National Park, the English Riviera, and the North Devon coastline drawing visitors year-round. For businesses in these sectors, organic search visibility is not a luxury — it is the primary channel through which customers discover and choose providers.

The county also has a growing tech scene, particularly around Exeter's Science Park and the SETsquared business incubator. These businesses need SEO strategies that match their ambition and help them compete nationally, not just locally.

Working with an experienced SEO consultant who understands Devon's economic landscape gives you a clear advantage over competitors still relying on outdated tactics or generic agency packages.

## Why choose an independent SEO consultant

Most agencies serving Devon businesses bundle SEO with web design, social media, and PPC advertising. The result is often a generalist approach where SEO gets a fraction of the attention it deserves.

When you work with me, you get a dedicated SEO specialist with deep experience in technical SEO, semantic content strategy, and [topical authority](/services/topical-authority/) building. Every recommendation I make is grounded in data from tools like Ahrefs, Google Search Console, and custom analytics setups.

The practical benefits of working with an independent consultant include:

- **Direct access** — You speak to me, not an account manager. Every call, every email, every report comes from the person doing the work.
- **Senior strategy from day one** — No juniors learning on your account. I bring the strategic depth that agencies reserve for their biggest clients.
- **Better value** — Without agency office costs and management layers, my pricing reflects the actual work delivered.
- **Flexibility** — Monthly retainers, one-off audits, or project-based work. We structure things around what your business genuinely needs.

## SEO services for Devon businesses

I offer a focused range of SEO services designed to deliver measurable improvements in organic traffic and revenue. These are the core areas I work across with Devon clients:

**[Technical SEO audits](/services/technical-seo-audit/)** — A comprehensive review of your site's crawlability, indexation, Core Web Vitals, structured data, and internal linking. I identify what is holding your site back and provide a prioritised roadmap to fix it.

**[Semantic SEO and topical authority](/services/topical-authority/)** — Modern SEO rewards genuine expertise. I map out topic clusters, identify content gaps, and build strategies that demonstrate authority to Google's algorithms.

**[Ongoing SEO consulting](/services/seo-consulting/)** — Monthly retainer work covering strategy, implementation guidance, content planning, and performance reporting. This is the service that compounds over time.

**Keyword research and content strategy** — Data-driven keyword research that goes beyond search volume. I focus on commercial intent, topical relevance, and realistic ranking opportunities for your domain.

**[Local SEO](/services/local-seo/)** — For Devon businesses serving a local audience, I optimise Google Business Profiles, build local citation consistency, and develop location-relevant content strategies. This is particularly important for tourism, hospitality, and service-area businesses across the county.

## Devon sectors I work with

Devon's economy spans a wide range of sectors, and I have experience working with businesses that reflect the county's strengths:

**Tourism and hospitality** — Hotels, holiday lets, attractions, and experience providers depend heavily on organic search for bookings. I build SEO strategies that capture seasonal demand at the right time with the right content, from summer holiday searches to off-season breaks.

**Food and drink** — Devon has a thriving food and drink scene, from artisan producers to farm shops and restaurants. SEO for these businesses often combines local visibility with broader brand-building content.

**Property and holiday lets** — The holiday lettings market in Devon is fiercely competitive online. Strong technical SEO, well-optimised property pages, and authoritative content about the local area make the difference between visibility and obscurity.

**Education** — The University of Exeter and other education providers need SEO strategies that address informational search intent, build E-E-A-T signals, and compete for high-value course-related queries.

**Professional services** — Accountants, solicitors, financial advisers, and consultants across Devon need organic visibility to attract clients. A combination of local SEO and authoritative content marketing drives sustainable growth.

**Outdoor and leisure** — Devon's outdoor economy — surfing, walking, cycling, adventure sports — generates enormous search demand. Businesses in this space need content strategies that capture both informational and transactional queries.

## How we work together

I operate on a remote-first basis, which means geography is never a barrier. Most of my Devon clients work with me entirely over video calls, email, and shared documents. It keeps things efficient and means you are paying for SEO expertise, not travel time.

A typical engagement starts with a discovery call where I learn about your business, your goals, and your current SEO position. From there, I put together a tailored proposal with clear deliverables, timelines, and pricing. No generic packages — everything is built around your specific situation.

